title: Estimate Vaccine Effectiveness Based on Different Study Designs
text: vaccineff developed Pontificia Universidad Javeriana part Epiverse-TRACE initiative. vaccineff R package offers tools estimating vaccine effectiveness (VE), using series epidemiological designs including cohort studies, test-negative case-control, screening methods (Halloran, Longini, Struchiner 2010). current version package provides set features preparing, visualizing, managing cohort data, estimating vaccine effectiveness, assessing performance models. Test-negative design screening method included future versions.

title: vaccineff 0.0.4
text: {vaccineff 0.0.4} simplifies data handling using linelist objects. Tags assigned outcome, censoring, vaccine dates using function make_vaccineff_data(), reducing redundancy function input parameters. new pipeline includes following three functions complementary methods: summary plot. make_vaccineff_data(): function returns S3 object class vaccineff_data() study’s relevant information. also allows creation matched cohort control confounding variables setting match = TRUE passing appropriate exact nearest arguments. method summary() can used check cohort characteristics, matching balance, sizes matched, excluded, removed populations. plot_coverage(): function returns plot vaccine coverage cumulative coverage. population matched, plot includes resulting count doses matching. effectiveness(): function provides methods estimating VE using HRHR. summary estimation available via summary(), graphical representation methodology generated plot().

title: vaccineff 0.0.4
text: following functions longer accessible users, called within make_vaccineff_data(): make_immunization() match_cohort() plot() method returns log-log survival type plots receiving object type effectiveness. deprecates functions plot_survival() plot_loglog().

title: vaccineff 0.0.3
text: version introduces iterative matching routine within match_cohort(). adjusting exposure times pairs, new pairs created removed ones unmatched population. new matches inconsistent exposure times removed , procedure repeated new pairs can made. usage functions remains unchanged update.

title: vaccineff 0.0.2
text: number functions steps computing vaccine effectiveness drastically reduced {vaccineff 0.0.2}. new pipeline estimation now consists three main functions: make_immunization(): Prepares information immunization dates vaccine status. can handle multiple columns vaccine dates custom vaccine statuses. cases, returns name column selected immunizing custom name, provided. match_cohort(): function improved generalized reduce observation bias cohorts. default matching strategy static, based nearest exact characteristics using Mahalanobis distance. exposure times pairs adjusted matching. future releases, rolling calendar matching introduced accurate method account exposure times. function returns S3 object class match, summary balance cohorts can printed using summary() method. matched cohort can extracted using get_dataset() method. matched cohort contains necessary information estimate vaccine effectiveness. effectiveness(): Receives (matched) cohort estimates vaccine effectiveness using Hazard Ratio (HR). S3 object class effectiveness returned, compatible plot() summary() methods. Future releases provide relative risk (RR) alternative cases proportional hazards assumption satisfied.
